<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38213c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38213c">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38213c"> 213(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> an odd joy</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Outside the note is that of joy &mdash; the joy of Nature at her freshest. Inside, too, the note is one of joy. There is <mark>an awed joy</mark> in the eyes of the bunch of people &mdash; small, sturdy, and very dark &mdash; standing in a rather huddled line as close to each other as possible (in obedience to the group instinct as well as because room is scant) at the west end of the church, and facing west. <small> Rev W.S. Hunt, <a name="WSHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSHI"><cite title="source">India's Outcastes: A New Era</cite></a> (1924) 1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
